{"data":{"markdownRemark":null,"npmPackage":{"name":"gatsby-source-dropbox-paper","description":"A source plugin for Gatsby that pulls data from the Dropbox Paper API.","keywords":["gatsby","gatsby-plugin","cms","dropbox","paper","dropbox","jamstack"],"lastPublisher":{"name":"alexmacarthur","avatar":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/e39d6cb16789125a8ef3113bdeaabf49"},"repository":{"url":"https://github.com/alexmacarthur/gatsby-source-dropbox-paper"},"readme":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<h1 id=\"dropbox-paper-source-plugin-for-gatsby\"><a href=\"#dropbox-paper-source-plugin-for-gatsby\" aria-label=\"dropbox paper source plugin for gatsby permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Dropbox Paper Source Plugin for Gatsby</h1>\n<p>Use this plugin to pull data from a <a href=\"https://paper.dropbox.com/\">Dropbox Paper</a> account into a <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/\">Gatsby</a> site or application. </p>\n<h2 id=\"installation\"><a href=\"#installation\" aria-label=\"installation permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Installation</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Run <code class=\"language-text\">npm install gatsby-source-dropbox-paper</code>. </p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Get an access token for your Dropbox account, which can be generated <a href=\"https://dropbox.github.io/dropbox-api-v2-explorer\">here</a>. </p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>In your <code class=\"language-text\">gatsby-config.js</code> file, add the plugin and the access token to the <code class=\"language-text\">plugins</code> array: </p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">plugins<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        resolve<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"gatsby-source-dropbox-paper\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        options<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n            access_token<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"your-access-token\"</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>You’re all set!</p>\n<h2 id=\"usage\"><a href=\"#usage\" aria-label=\"usage permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Usage</h2>\n<h3 id=\"setting-output-format\"><a href=\"#setting-output-format\" aria-label=\"setting output format permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Setting Output Format</h3>\n<p>By default, data will be pulled in Markdown format, but you may also specify “html” by including a <code class=\"language-text\">format</code> option: </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">plugins<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n    <span class=\"token string\">'gatsby-plugin-react-helmet'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        resolve<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"gatsby-source-dropbox-paper\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        options<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n            access_token<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"your-access-token\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> \n            format<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"html\"</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"querying-for-data\"><a href=\"#querying-for-data\" aria-label=\"querying for data permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Querying for Data</h3>\n<p>You can use the following GraphQL fields to pull raw data into your pages. </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"graphql\"><pre class=\"language-graphql\"><code class=\"language-graphql\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    allDropboxPaperDocument<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token attr-name\">limit</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        edges <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n            node <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n                content<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n                doc_id<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n                owner<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> \n                title<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> \n                created_date<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n                status <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n                    _tag\n                <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> \n                revision<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> \n                last_updated_date<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> \n                last_editor<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> \n                id<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> \n                internal <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n                    type<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> \n                    content<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> \n                    contentDigest<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> \n                    owner\n                <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n            <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<h4 id=\"get-transformed-markdown\"><a href=\"#get-transformed-markdown\" aria-label=\"get transformed markdown permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Get Transformed Markdown</h4>\n<p>Using the <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/packages/gatsby-transformer-remark/\">gatsby-transformer-remark</a> plugin, you can access pulled Markdown transformed into HTML. Simply use the <code class=\"language-text\">childMarkdownRemark</code> field when querying for data. </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"graphql\"><pre class=\"language-graphql\"><code class=\"language-graphql\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    allDropboxPaperDocument<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token attr-name\">limit</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        edges <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n            node <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n              \tchildMarkdownRemark <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n                    id<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n                    html<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> \n                    excerpt<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> \n                    timeToRead<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> \n                    wordCount <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n                        paragraphs\n                        sentences\n                        words\n                    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n              \t<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n            <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"the-future\"><a href=\"#the-future\" aria-label=\"the future permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>The Future</h2>\n<p>Right now, this plugin pulls <em>all</em> documents from an authenticated account, which is less than ideal. Improvements will come with changes to this plugin, as well as the evolution of the <a href=\"https://www.dropbox.com/developers\">Dropbox API</a>, which has limited capabilities in terms of filtering documents to be pulled. Here’s what I’d like to see in the future: </p>\n<ul>\n<li>The ability pull documents by status. </li>\n<li>The ability to pull documents by specific directory. </li>\n<li>Other stuff. </li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"contributions\"><a href=\"#contributions\" aria-label=\"contributions permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Contributions</h2>\n<p>Please do!</p>\n<h2 id=\"license\"><a href=\"#license\" aria-label=\"license permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>License</h2>\n<p>MIT © <a href=\"https://macarthur.me\">Alex MacArthur</a></p>","timeToRead":2}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/packages/gatsby-source-dropbox-paper/","id":"0ef76535-beb3-55a7-abb9-d382879f0a53","layout":"plugins"}}